---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
	title="Terms of Use | URLX"
	description="Terms of use for URLX, a no-account URL shortener."
>
	<section class="bg-white">
		<div class="mx-auto w-full max-w-[800px] px-6 py-16">
			<p class="text-[14px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.06em] text-ink-2">
				Last updated June 22, 2026
			</p>
			<h1 class="mt-3 text-[40px] font-semibold leading-tight text-ink">
				Terms of Use
			</h1>
			<div class="mt-8 space-y-8 text-[16px] leading-7 text-ink-2">
				<section>
					<h2 class="text-[22px] font-semibold text-ink">Agreement</h2>
					<p class="mt-3">
						These Terms of Use apply when you access URLX, create or open a
						short link, convert a webpage, inspect URL metadata, or use the URLX
						API. If you do not agree to these terms, do not use URLX.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2 class="text-[22px] font-semibold text-ink">The Service</h2>
					<p class="mt-3">
						URLX provides URL utilities, including short links and conversion of
						public webpages to Markdown or rendered HTML, plus metadata
						inspection for public webpages. Conversion and metadata results may
						be incomplete, outdated, or unavailable when a website blocks
						automated access. URLX does not endorse, control, or guarantee
						third-party websites or the accuracy or safety of converted content
						or extracted metadata.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2 class="text-[22px] font-semibold text-ink">User Responsibility</h2>
					<p class="mt-3">
						You are responsible for the URLs you submit, how you share short
						links, and how you use converted content or metadata results. You
						must have the rights and permissions needed to submit, reproduce,
						download, publish, or share the relevant URLs and content.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2 class="text-[22px] font-semibold text-ink">Prohibited Uses</h2>
					<p class="mt-3">You may not use URLX to create, share, or support:</p>
					<ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
						<li>phishing, credential theft, impersonation, or deceptive redirects;</li>
						<li>malware, drive-by downloads, botnets, or exploit delivery;</li>
						<li>spam, unsolicited bulk messaging, or abusive automation;</li>
						<li>harassment, threats, doxxing, or unlawful surveillance;</li>
						<li>child sexual abuse material or sexual exploitation;</li>
						<li>content or activity that violates applicable law;</li>
						<li>copyright, trademark, privacy, publicity, or other rights infringement;</li>
						<li>attempts to bypass URLX security, rate limits, or abuse controls;</li>
						<li>links that hide the true destination for fraud or other harmful conduct.</li>
					</ul>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2 class="text-[22px] font-semibold text-ink">Moderation And Removal</h2>
					<p class="mt-3">
						URLX may disable, remove, or refuse short links at any time,
						including when a link appears abusive, illegal, harmful, unsafe, or
						in violation of these terms. URLX may also preserve and disclose
						information when reasonably necessary to investigate abuse, protect
						the service, comply with law, or enforce these terms.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2 class="text-[22px] font-semibold text-ink">Abuse Reports</h2>
					<p class="mt-3">
						To report abuse, send the short URL, the destination URL if known,
						and the reason for the report to the URLX maintainers using the
						maintainer links in the footer. Copyright owners should include
						enough information to identify the copyrighted work, the allegedly
						infringing link, contact information, and a good-faith statement
						that the use is unauthorized.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2 class="text-[22px] font-semibold text-ink">No Reliance On Links</h2>
					<p class="mt-3">
						Short links may point to third-party websites. You should use your
						own judgment before opening or relying on any destination website.
						URLX is not responsible for third-party content, products, services,
						security practices, or privacy practices.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2 class="text-[22px] font-semibold text-ink">Availability</h2>
					<p class="mt-3">
						URLX is provided on an as-available basis. The service may change,
						break, lose data, become unavailable, or stop operating. URLX is not
						obligated to maintain any particular short link forever.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2 class="text-[22px] font-semibold text-ink">Disclaimers</h2>
					<p class="mt-3">
						URLX is provided "as is" and "as available" without warranties of
						any kind, whether express, implied, or statutory, including implied
						warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose,
						title, and non-infringement.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2 class="text-[22px] font-semibold text-ink">Limitation Of Liability</h2>
					<p class="mt-3">
						To the maximum extent permitted by law, URLX and its maintainers
						will not be liable for indirect, incidental, special, consequential,
						exemplary, or punitive damages, or for lost profits, data, goodwill,
						or business opportunities arising from or related to use of URLX.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2 class="text-[22px] font-semibold text-ink">Indemnity</h2>
					<p class="mt-3">
						You agree to defend, indemnify, and hold harmless URLX and its
						maintainers from claims, damages, liabilities, losses, costs, and
						expenses arising from your submitted URLs, your short links, your
						use of URLX, or your violation of these terms.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2 class="text-[22px] font-semibold text-ink">Changes</h2>
					<p class="mt-3">
						URLX may update these terms. Continued use of URLX after an update
						means you accept the updated terms.
					</p>
				</section>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
</Layout>
